Check the pod logs for issues using 'kubectl logs pod-name>'.
Run 'kubectl get rs' to check the status of the ReplicaSet.
Execute 'kubectl get svc' to check the service configuration.
Check that the NodePort and firewall settings are accurate.
Use 'kubectl get nodes' to check the health of the nodes.
Examine cloud security settings.
Verify application settings and code.
Test internal access from a debug pod.
Look at external access concerns such as network or firewall
Check the service and deployment YAML files for configuration mistakes.
